The correct numbers as of last Fall are: None/No response 30% Catholic 28% Other 19% Lutheran 11% Other Christian 7.6% Muslim 2.1% Buddhist 1.5% Hindu .4% Jewish .4% If it's possible to indicate, "Enrolled students survey, 2018," that would be helpful. incident.name: Create COURSE_CATALOG table in Webpublishing database and grant user "catalog" Select permission
incident.description: We need to make the semester courses live for the catalog and make the trimester courses no longer show.  Below is a the syntax to make the new courses and some of the other courses that did not get the new date of '06/01/19' to also show, since we kept some courses active if nothing was changing about them.  Justin, could you update the website to use the revised syntax?  Please let me know if you have any questions, also if you could also let Liesl and myself know when this is done.   --CREATE COURSE_CATALOG TABLE IN WEBPUBLISHING USING THE FOLLOWING STORED PROCEDURE.  SCHEDULE TO UPDATE NIGHTLY.-- SELECT CRS.COURSES_ID, CRS_TITLE,  CRS_NAME, REPLACE(CAST(CRS_DESC AS VARCHAR(1500)),CHAR(253),' ') AS CRS_DESC,  CRS_MIN_CRED,  CRS_MAX_CRED,  PREREQ.ACR_PRINTED_SPEC AS PREREQS  FROM COURSES AS CRS LEFT JOIN (SELECT POS, COURSES_ID, CRS_STATUS FROM APPROVAL_STATUS            WHERE POS = '1') AS STAT ON CRS.COURSES_ID = STAT.COURSES_ID LEFT JOIN ACAD_REQMTS AS PREREQ ON CRS.CRS_PREREQS = PREREQ.ACAD_REQMTS_ID LEFT JOIN (SELECT * FROM COURSE_CONTACT           WHERE POS = '1')  AS CC ON CRS.COURSES_ID = CC.COURSES_ID  LEFT JOIN (SELECT * FROM COURSES_LS            WHERE CRS_COURSE_TYPES = 'PEA') AS CSTYPE ON CRS.COURSES_ID = CSTYPE.COURSES_ID   WHERE (CRS_START_DATE = '06/01/19' OR CC.CRS_INSTR_METHODS IN ('INL','DIR','IND') OR   (CRS_NAME LIKE 'MULS-%' OR CRS_NAME LIKE 'MUCH-%' OR CRS_NAME LIKE 'MUEN-%')   OR CRS_COURSE_TYPES = 'PEA') AND CRS_END_DATE IS NULL ORDER BY CRS_NAME

incident.name: AIMS8 application and database moved to Midgard
incident.description: With help from the vendor: The website is https://aimsparking.com/ The support person :  Mike Tyszka The phone number is:  800-886-6316 The support email address is:  support@aimsparking.com The application and database are now on the server Midgard in the database MIDGARD\sqlserver2012. The people who have the client installed are:  Trisha Hines_Morrison and two other PCs in facilities, the dispatch PC, Mark, and Tom in security.  Also Tammy and Jana have it on their PCs in ITS. In order for client to work on the PCs the following change was made: In the directory C:\Program Files\AIMS, there is a file called api.config.  This file needs to have one word edited.  Where it says "fulla" needs to be changed to "midgard".  Once the change has been made and saved, you can start the Aims software.  The first time the software is started, you will get a message that the software is out of date.  Click OK.  Let it do it's thing.   When it is finished you will be presented with the login window.   NOTE:  The logins are not "LDAP", so someone has to set these up in the application. The AIMS application is a version 8; however, version 9 is the current version, so an upgrade is recommended. We still need to set up a new student import into Aims and new layout.  The vendor said they can help.
